This implements a Storage class to handle saving to and loading from storage, and adds a human-readable serialization/deserialization interface for Expenditures. The main MindMyMoney loop is also modified to save the expenditure list after a successful command is run.
This implements basic tests for Expenditure and Storage. It also modifies the two classes to make them more testable.
This fixes a few error messages that weren't updated along with the associated code. This also adds basic tests for UpdateCommands.

commitResults.messageBody:
The former implementation of save/load is coupled with the AddCommand implementation, which may create problems if information that cannot be encoded using add needs to be saved.
